{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480895","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480895"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:53:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:53:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"122"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"122","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/122"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.69,0.04,0.06,0.08,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"122"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104156"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"122","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/122"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"122"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86479"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"188"},{"type":"tags","id":"2341"},{"type":"tags","id":"4952"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"11624"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12914"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"13773"},{"type":"contributions","id":"30598"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37385"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39437"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41995"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104156","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/104156"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 19-year-old man is brought into the Emergency Department by his girlfriend for unusual behaviour. He claims that the Government is trying to steal his idea for his upcoming architecture project and he has created a fort in his room and taped the windows shut to protect his project. He has been skipping his classes for the past two weeks in fear that someone will come into his room while he is out, and he is no longer motivated to work on his project if someone is planning on stealing it. He does not have any known medical conditions, and does not take any regular medications. Throughout the consultation, he does not say much and displays blunted affect.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Urine toxicology screen","Contact his parents","Reassurance that the Government does not want to steal his project","Intramuscular olanzapine","Detention under an Inpatient Treatment Order"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn this age group, substance use and abuse is the most common cause of psychosis. It is estimated that drugs or alcohol abuse are involved in nearly 40% of cases of first episode of psychosis. With the steadily increasing availability and use of illicit drugs such as cannabis and methamphetamine, this percentage is likely to increase. Working on this principle, the first action to be taken is to do a \u003Cstrong\u003Eurinary drug screen\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe patient has reduced capacity to determine what is real and what is not real. He has lost insight into the functional nature of his beliefs and this has led to disparity in his consideration of reality. Care must be taken and attempts to invalidate his beliefs may undermine rapport with him and his willingness to participate voluntarily.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHe is not posing outward harm to himself or people surrounding him, and therefore it is not necessary to either \u003Cstrong\u003Edetain him\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003Eadminister intramuscular medication\u003C/strong\u003E. There is no mention of him refusing a voluntary admission.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough the patient does not have capacity, he is a legal adult and and hence his \u003Cstrong\u003Eparents\u003C/strong\u003E do not need to be involved unless he requests so.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Substance abuse is a common cause of psychosis in the younger age groups.","A urine toxicology screen is an essential first-line investigation in young adults presenting with first-episode psychosis.","Building rapport and maintaining a therapeutic relationship is crucial when managing patients with psychotic symptoms."],"references":["Tucker P. Substance misuse and early psychosis. Australas Psychiatry 2009; 17:291-94. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19301164/","Fiorentini A, Cant\u00f9 F, Crisanti C, Cereda G, Oldani L, Brambilla P. Substance-Induced Psychoses: An Updated Literature Review. Front Psychiatry. 2021 Dec 23;12:694863. doi: 10.3389/fpsyt.2021.694863. PMID: 35002789; PMCID: PMC8732862. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35002789/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86479"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"122"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"86479","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/86479"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-05-29T16:39:49+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-05-29T17:11:47+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"122"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"104156"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{